			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Title:</strong><br />
Lead Experience Architect (LXA)&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>The Role:</strong><br />
We are seeking a fulltime lead experience architect, also known as sr user experience designer or an interaction designer, for a large northwest aerospace client. You will serve as the point of contact for your respective client group and be tasked with envisioning (&amp; designing) sleek and simple experiences for mission critical applications.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate will thrive in a work environment, which requires independent self-direction, coupled with an aptitude for team collaboration and open communication. The candidate will also have experience or a desire to learn to navigate complex political environments &ndash; in addition to a thorough understanding of contemporary user-centered design methodologies.</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:<br />
Soft Skills</strong><br />
&bull; Collaborate with back-end devs, front-end devs &amp; visual designers &ndash; to bring all of your ideas to life.<br />
&bull; Working with project managers and product managers to balance business needs with political timelines.<br />
&bull; Facilitating dialog around and gathering end-user requirements and business requirements.<br />
&bull; Guiding clients through the engagement process and managing their expectations.<br />
&bull; Researching interaction design and technology trends.<br />
&bull; Strong conceptualization ability.</p>
<p>
<strong>Hard Skills</strong><br />
&bull; 4+ years of ux design experience for software, web applications, consumer electronics and/or mobile devices.<br />
&bull; Focused on creating UX deliverables: wireframes, sitemaps, personas and task flows etc.<br />
&bull; Strong working knowledge of Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Fireworks and associated design tools.<br />
&bull; Familiar with user interface design patterns and standard UCD methodologies across multiple platforms.<br />
&bull; Responsible for the execution of strong interaction design and an attention to detail.<br />
&bull; Developing interaction models and conceptual frameworks.<br />
&bull; Performing user research.<br />
&bull; Strong written and verbal communication skills.<br />
&bull; Strong client facing presentation and communication skills.<br />
&bull; Strong understanding of common software development and software project management practices.</p>
<p>
<strong>Pluses:</strong><br />
&bull; An eye for clean, branded visual design &ndash; even if this is not your UX focus.<br />
&bull; An understanding of how applications are built &ndash; from a development &amp; architecture standpoint.<br />
&bull; Digital agency / client experience.<br />
&bull; Bachelor/Master Degree in Interaction Design, New Media Design, Industrial Design, HCI, Human Factors or related field.<br />
&bull; Strong familiarity with new technologies and nascent interface design approaches.</p>
<p>
<strong>Additional:</strong><br />
&bull; Occasional travel, but not typically a focus.<br />
&bull; Work is on-site with remote flexibility when needed.<br />
&bull; Please apply with a portfolio url or pdf showing depth and breadth of UX related work.</p>
]]></description>
